    "created_at": "2016-01-23T12:11:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-01-23T12:11:23Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> What's the point of having this both as sequence and both as a trait flag? It kinda confuses me at the moment.\n\nIt's needed on sequences to make the sequence loader compile and load sequences accordingly.\n\nAnd I think it's better to be able to switch it on/off per-actor as well, if only because only 2 mods need it and it's essentially just a hack to work around WW's weird rendering perspective, so I'd feel uncomfortable to have it tick away without use in D2k/TS/3rd-party mods. \n@pchote might have some other reason(s) as well.\n"
  },
